==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nudibranchiata
<hw>Nu`di*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Nude</er>, and <er>Branchia</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of opisthobranchiate mollusks, having
no shell except while very young. The gills are naked and situated upon
the back or sides. See <er>Ceratobranchia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nudibranchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
